Is that your end goal?

00:00:43.309 --> 00:00:45.078
No!

00:00:45.111 --> 00:00:46.546
-Okay, that...
-Okay. (laughs)

00:00:46.579 --> 00:00:49.215
No, our-our goal
is definitely not to change, uh,

00:00:49.248 --> 00:00:51.617
you know, the red states pink,
you know?

00:00:51.650 --> 00:00:53.953
We just want to make sure
that they open their hearts

00:00:53.986 --> 00:00:56.155
-a little bit. -So you-you w...
you're going out there

00:00:56.188 --> 00:00:58.424
-to try to change parts
of America. -Yeah.

00:00:58.457 --> 00:01:00.760
Well, no, we're not trying
to change parts of America.

00:01:00.793 --> 00:01:03.763
We're trying to make people
feel better about who they are

00:01:03.796 --> 00:01:05.565
so that, hopefully,
they'll change themselves.

00:01:05.598 --> 00:01:07.100
How do you have the hard
conversation with yourself

00:01:07.133 --> 00:01:08.701
so you can have a hard
conversation with other people?

00:01:08.734 --> 00:01:10.303
How<i> do</i> you have a hard
conversation with yourself?

00:01:10.336 --> 00:01:11.504
Well, let's start
with your father.

00:01:11.537 --> 00:01:13.039
-Please, okay, let's...
That was... -Okay?

00:01:13.072 --> 00:01:15.441
How do<i> you</i> have a
hard conversation with<i> yourself?</i>

00:01:15.474 --> 00:01:17.710
-We start with<i> my</i> father.
-You start with your...

00:01:17.743 --> 00:01:19.779
-It-it all starts there.
-It starts from the top down.

00:01:19.812 --> 00:01:22.048
-Yeah. Uh-huh. -You-you are...
You cover culture.

00:01:22.081 --> 00:01:24.183
-Yes. -Now, that's something
I've never been that into.

00:01:24.216 --> 00:01:26.519
